article.headline: Tennessee Tech 79, Austin Peay 75
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher and Belton Rivers combined for 42 points to help Tennessee Tech hold off a second-half comeback by Austin Peay and win 79-75 Monday night. Tennessee Tech (12-5, 7-2 Ohio Valley Conference) was up 48-27 at the half on 69.2 percent shooting from the field and hitting 9-of-13 3-point attempts. But the Governors (10-7, 5-2) went on a 29-4 run in the second half to cut it to 61-53 with 10:36 left. Zach Schlader led with 16 points, Derek Wright and Fernandez Lockett each had 15 and Todd Babington 14. Schlader put the Governors within 2 points twice in the final three minutes, and a layup by Babington closed Tech's lead to 77-75 with 1:07 to go. But the Golden Eagles took advantage of a pair of fouls to go up for the final score and Schlader pitched the ball out of bounds with three seconds left. Tech had a slight edge in boards, 34-30. Fisher had 22 points and Rivers 20, including a pair of layups and a free throw in the final four minutes.
